'''Havitta''' is a name used to refer the ancient Buddhist stupas in Maldives. The word ''Haviita'' is believed to have some affinities with the [[Sanskrit]] word '''Caitya''' used to refer Buddhist sacred places.<ref>[http://www.persee.fr/web/revues/home/prescript/article/befeo_0336-1519_1987_num_76_1_1726]</ref><ref>[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/88605/caitya]</ref> Some of the famous Havittas in Maldives include '''[[Fua Mulaku Havitta]]''' and '''Vādū Havitta'''.
